translated: Axelson, Carl Ove Alphons, editor, Jönköping, born January 23rd, 1895 in Jönköping to parents Axel Gustafsson and Ada Josefina Bengtsson. Married to Siri Peterson in 1935. They had a son named Rolf, born in 1937. He attended a commercial college. He was employed at Bergmans Bookstore in Jönköping from 1913 to 1915, worked at the Jönköping city accountant's office from 1915 to 1918, and was a collaborator at Småland's Allehanda from 1918. He was the secretary there from 1920 to 1944. He was the secretary of the Jönköping radio club and a member of its board since 1927, program director for Jönköping radio station from 1933 to 1934, and involved with the Jönköping radio club since 1933. He was an honorary member of the Jönköping scout troop, a former member of the Jönköping right-wing association board, the Swedish Motorist Club board, the Jönköping southern property owners' association board, the Jönköping traffic association, on the board of directors of the Friends of the Old Poor association, board of the Jönköping Scout Group Benevolent Association, and a member of the Swedish Journalist Association. He used the signatures -c, Nic, O.A. Hobbres, and was interested in philately, fishing, and motorsport. He was awarded the Swedish Scout Association White Hedging Badge and PatrGM.
